        {
            "text": "Although there are studies that failed to find a relationship [10,[15][16][17][18][19][20], inflammatory cytokines such as C-reactive protein (CRP), tumor necrosis factor-\u03b1 (TNF-\u03b1), and interleukin (IL)-6 were found to be inversely associated with vitamin D levels [21][22][23][24][25]. ",
